🔹 Demultiplexer (DEMUX)

Opposite of MUX:

👉 One input → multiple outputs

🔹 Encoder

Converts:
👉 Multiple inputs → binary code

Example:
8 inputs → 3-bit output

🔹 Decoder

Converts:
👉 Binary input → one active output

Example:
3-to-8 decoder

🔹 Priority Encoder

Handles multiple active inputs:

👉 Gives priority to highest-order input

🔹 Comparator

Compares two numbers:

Outputs:

A > B

A = B

A < B

